      <div class="article-teaser">
        We started managing the Liverpool Street to Shenfield rail service in May 2015. We also took over the running of 11 stations between Acton Main Line and Taplow (excluding Slough station) in December 2017.
        
      </div>
    
    <div class="on-this-page">
      <p>Since taking over the Liverpool Street to Shenfield service we have:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Seen passenger journeys increase to more than 47 million in 2016/17 from 38 million in 2015/16</li>
    <li>Made sure there are staff on duty at every station from first train to last</li>
    <li>Provided cleaner trains and better customer information</li>
    <li>Tackled fare evasion and antisocial behaviour in partnership with the British Transport Police</li>
    <li>Improved reliability and the integration of these routes into the rest of London's public transport network</li>
</ul>
<p>We introduced new trains on the route in 2017. See what <a href="/travel-information/improvements-and-projects/tfl-rail-improvements">other improvements we're making to TfL Rail</a>.</p>
<h2>New services</h2>
<p>TfL took over the stopping services between Paddington and Heathrow terminals 2, 3 and 4, from Heathrow Connect and Great Western Railway (GWR). This is part of another major milestone for the Elizabeth line staged opening programme.</p>
<p>Currently operating as TfL Rail, these services will form part of the <a href="/travel-information/improvements-and-projects/elizabeth-line">Elizabeth line</a> when it launches.</p>
